<topic id="change-order-in-maps">
  <title>Change the Order of Topics in DITA Maps</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>DITA<indexterm>Maps<indexterm>Change order of
          topics</indexterm></indexterm></indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p id="p_pll_dgk_54b">You can change the order and nesting of the topics in a map in several ways:<ul
        id="ul_dsm_c3v_1q">
        <li id="li_qll_dgk_54b" irina="irina">By dragging and dropping topics within the <xref
            href="dita-maps-manager.dita#dita-maps-manager"><uicontrol>DITA Maps
            Manager</uicontrol></xref>.</li>
        <li product="author editor" id="li_rll_dgk_54b" irina="irina">By highlighting a topic in the <xref
            href="dita-maps-manager.dita#dita-maps-manager"><uicontrol>DITA Maps
            Manager</uicontrol></xref>, holding down the
            <uicontrol><shortcut>Alt</shortcut></uicontrol> key, and pressing the arrow keys.</li>
        <li id="li_sll_dgk_54b" irina="irina">By showing the extended <xref href="dita-maps-manager.dita#dita-maps-manager"
              ><uicontrol>DITA Maps Manager</uicontrol></xref> toolbar (click the <uicontrol><image
              href="../img/Settings16.png" id="image_xyt_t3v_1q"/>Settings</uicontrol> icon on the
            <xref href="dita-maps-manager.dita#dita-maps-manager"><uicontrol>DITA Maps
              Manager</uicontrol></xref> toolbar and select the extended toolbar) and then using the
          node moving buttons (<image href="../img/NodeUp16.png" id="image_phk_dmq_js"/><image
            href="../img/NodeDown16.png" id="image_yc5_dmq_js"/><image
            href="../img/NodePromote16.png" id="image_w2c_2mq_js"/><image
            href="../img/NodeDemote16.png" id="image_dnj_2mq_js"/>) on the toolbar to move topics
          around in the map.</li>
      </ul>To understand how to organize topics in a <term keyref="glossentry_ditamap">DITA
        map</term> using the <xref href="dita-maps-manager.dita#dita-maps-manager"><uicontrol>DITA
          Maps Manager</uicontrol></xref>, you can examine and experiment with the sample map called
        <filepath>flowers.ditamap</filepath>, located in the <filepath><term
          conkeyref="reusables-user-guide/oxy-install-dir"/>/samples/dita</filepath> folder.</p>
  </body>
</topic>
